The Palace of the Olu of Warri has refuted speculation about the demise of Olu of Warri, Ogiame Ikenwoli. This was made known in an official statement by the Director of Palace Administration, Chief Clement Maleghemi. He made this disclosure in an official statement signed and made available to newsmen on Tuesday, December 23, 2020, in Warri. Maleghemi said that the monarch was indisposed and currently receiving medical attention by a team of qualified specialists. “The attention of the Palace of His Royal Majesty, Ogiame Ikenwoli, the Olu of Warri has been drawn to News/social media publications announcing the sudden demise of His Majesty. “We wish to notify the general public that His Majesty is indisposed and currently receiving medical attention by a team of qualified specialists. “Any further information on the subject would be made known to the general public by the Office of the Traditional Prime Minister of Warri Kingdom, Chief Ayiri Emami, the Ologbotsere of Warri Kingdom,” Maleghemi said.